{
  "texts": [
    "NER researchers mostly do data cleaning to clean up data, including punctuation mark deletion, hashtags, URL removal, and excess space removal.",
    "The most common tokenization technique is white space to break raw text data into tokens.",
    "Tokenization is the most preferred choice in the NER preprocessing stage; it prepares the manuscript for NER annotation.",
    "The entity detection process is carried out on tokens generated by this preprocessing stage.",
    "Spaces-based tokenization is excellent for Romantype-based languages like English and Indonesian.A large dataset/corpus is generally performed segmentation, breaking the large corpus into smaller units [66]."
  ]
}